<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="662" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/482: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-07T17:00:00-05:00">October 7, 1938—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>262. Peiping’s 601, October 4, 4 p.m., in regard to identification of
                            American properties in certain north China areas. The Department offers
                            for your consideration the suggestion that the Americans responsible for
                            American properties in the areas indicated in the Japanese communication
                            might well be advised to keep their property markers from becoming so
                            weather-worn as to be indistinct.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
